hen a massive fire at a chevron refinery in richmond california sent toxic smoke billowing into the air about  miles northeast of san francisco in the aftermath more than  people sought medical treatment for respiratory problems on monday chevron pleaded no contest to six criminal charges related to the fire and agreed to submit to additional oversight over the next few years and pay  million in fines and restitution as part of a plea deal with state and county prosecutors two days earlier thousands of people marched to condemn safety issues at chevron’s plant and to call for renewable alternatives to fossil fuels   chevron pays m fines and pleads no contest to richmond fire charges associated press report appearing in the guardian  august  retrieved  august    chevron takes responsibility for brazil oil spill may face m fine foxnewscom november   archived from the original on  retrieved october     chevron takes full responsibility for brazil oil spill bbccouk november     chevron faces bn brazil legal suit over oil spill bbc news december   on march   the brazilian federal justice prohibited  key people including george buck and other foreigners connected to chevron brazil from leaving the country without judicial permission because of evident guilt on the  oil spills   chevron and brazil reach deal on oil spill  nytimescom   chevron to pay  million for brazil oil spill   exclusive riggers sought evacuation before deadly chevron blast reuters july     schmidt kathrine january   chevron prepares to drill nigeria relief well upstream online nhst media group subscription required retrieved january     chevron suspends survey after fire in bangladesh   chevron resumes survey after fire in bangladesh  reuters   blokuj badania ws ³upków chevron pozywa mieszkañców lubelszczyzny to jest wojna gazetapl archived from the original on  retrieved april     polish tvp interview and material about gas exploration in poland first broadcast in wiadomosci on   przez łupki premier t