chevron and weyerhaeuser created catchlight energy llc which researches the conversion of cellulosebased biomass into biofuels in  the catchlight plan was downsized due to competition with fossil fuel projects for funds between  and  chevron contributed up to  million to a strategic research alliance with the georgia institute of technology to develop cellulosic biofuels and to create a process to convert biomass like wood or switchgrass into fuels additionally chevron holds a  stake in galveston bay biodiesel lp which produces up to  million us gallons  m of renewable biodiesel fuel a year in  the chevron announced a  kw photovoltaic demonstration project in bakersfield california called project brightfield for exploring possibilities to use solar power for powering chevrons facilities it consists of technologies from seven companies which chevron is evaluating for largescale use in fellows california chevron has invested in the  kw solarmine photovoltaic solar project which supplies daytime power to the midwaysunset oil field in questa chevron has built a  mw concentrated photovoltaic plant that comprises  solar arrays which use fresnel lenses in october  chevron launched a mw thermal solartosteam facility in the coalinga field to produce the steam for enhanced oil recovery as of  the project is the largest of its kind in the world in  chevron began reducing its investment in renewable energy technologies reducing headcount and selling alternative energyrelated assets corporate affairsedit financeedit for the fiscal year  chevron reported earnings of us billion with an annual revenue of us billion an increase of  over the previous fiscal cycle chevrons shares traded at over  per share and its market capitalization was valued at over us billion headquartersedit chevron tower in houston chevrons corporate headquarters are located in a acre campus in san ramon california the company moved there from its earlier headquarters at  market street in san francisco californ